  "prompt": "How should a 2 month old puppy be trained?",
  "response": "Training a 2-month-old puppy should focus on basic socialization and foundational skills:\n\n1. Socialization\n- Expose puppy to different people, animals, and environments\n- Ensure positive, gentle interactions\n- Help puppy become comfortable with various sounds and experiences\n\n2. House Training\n- Take puppy outside frequently (every 1-2 hours)\n- Use consistent potty spot\n- Praise and reward immediately after successful potty\n- Watch for signs they need to go (sniffing, circling)\n\n3. Basic Commands\n- Start with simple commands like \"sit\" and \"come\"\n- Use short, positive training sessions (5-10 minutes)\n- Use treats and praise as rewards\n- Be patient and consistent\n\n4. Crate Training\n- Introduce crate as a safe, comfortable space\n- Make crate positive with treats and toys\n- Use for short periods initially\n- Never use as punishment\n\n5. Bite Inhibition\n- Teach gentle play\n- Redirect biting to appropriate chew toys\n- Make a high-pitched yelp when puppy bites too hard\n\n6. Leash Training\n- Start with short, positive sessions\n- Use treats to encourage walking beside you\n- Be patient and consistent\n\nRemember: Keep training sessions short, positive, and fun.",
